[[Sant]] [[Kavi]] '''Jagjivan Das''' (or '''Jagiwan Das''',<ref name=russell>Robert Vane Russell, [http://books.google.com/books?id=jVXhAAAAMAAJ&pg=PA307 ''The tribes and castes of the Central Provinces of India, Volume 1''], [[Macmillan and Company]], 1916, pp307-8 (retrieved 20 February 2012 from [[Google Books]])</ref> 1727 [[Sardaha]],<ref name=barabanki>[http://barabanki.nic.in/person.htm Personalities], [[Barabanki district]]</ref> [[Chas]] - 1761)<ref name=russell/> is the founder of the [[Satnami]] [[Hindu sect]]<ref name=barabanki/> of Upper India.<ref name=russell/>

Das was born on the banks of the [[Ghaghra River]] at the village of Sardaha.<ref name=barabanki/> However, he made [[Kotwa]] his spiritual and literary birth place and meditorium.<ref name=barabanki/> He founded the Satnaami sect, popularly known as Kotwa [[Dham]], 6km southeast of Kotwa in [[Badosarai]])<ref>[indianetzone.com/47/tourism_barabanki_district.htm Tourism in Barabanki District], [[Indianetzone]]</ref> Leading a family life, Sant Kavi Jagjivan Das proved to be a great saint and literary genius.<ref name=barabanki/> To his credit are more than a dozen literary creations, which have enriched the heritage of [[Hindi literature]].<ref name=barabanki/>

==Works==
His important works are:<ref name=barabanki/>

* ''Agh Vinaash''
* ''Maha Pralay''
* ''Gyan Prakash''
* ''Shabd-Sagar''
* ''Param Granth''
* ''Prem-Path''
* ''Aagam Paddhati''
{{multicol-break}}

==Pupils==
His pupils are:<ref name=barabanki/>
* [[Bodhe Das]]
* [[Dulan Das]]
* [[Devi Das]]
* [[Naval Das]]
* [[Aahalaad Das]]
* [[Bhikha Das]]

And others who went on to become famous literary and spiritual personalities themselves.<ref name=barabanki/>
{{multicol-end}}

